    • Field Detail

      • key

        public final java.lang.String key
        The key.

      • element

        public final org.w3c.dom.Element element
        A stand-alone topicref which is the definition of the key. May be completely empty (no content, no attributes).

        The href attribute, if any, contains an absolute URI. If it points to a topic, this URI ends with #topic_id. (That is, the href attribute is ready-to-use.)

        This element has a ditac:absoluteHref="true" if the href attribute was specified by the DITA author as an absolute URI.

      • fromChildKeySpace

        public final int fromChildKeySpace
        Strictly positive if this key definition has been copied from a child key space. Value is 1 if it comes for a child, 2 if it comes from a grand-child, etc.

      • getHref

        public java.lang.String getHref()
        returns the absolute URI corresponding to key. May return null.

        This URI, if any, ends with #topic_id if specified key designates a topic.

      • isAbsoluteHref

        public boolean isAbsoluteHref()
        Returns true if the href attribute contained an absolute URL as its value; false otherwise.

        This method is needed because getHref() always returns an absolute location.

      • getURL

        public java.net.URL getURL()
